Parliament, Thursday, 14 November 2019 – Mr Jerome Joseph Maake was appointed as the chairperson of the Joint Standing Committee on Intelligence (JSCI) on 30 October 2019, in terms of section 2 of the Intelligence Services Oversight Act,1994(Act No 40 of 1994). The following members were appointed to the Joint Standing Committee on Intelligence on 30 October 2019, in terms of section 2 of the Intelligence Services Oversight Act, 1994 (Act No 40 of 1994): ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE JSCI, MR JJ MAAKE. For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
